024/**
025 * A generic linked hash set with with a fast implementation, originally from fastutil as ObjectLinkedOpenHashSet but
026 * modified to support indexed access of items, reordering, and optional hash strategies for array keys (which fastutil
027 * does differently).
028 * <p>
029 * Instances of this class use a hash table to represent a set. The table is
030 * filled up to a specified <em>load factor</em>, and then doubled in size to
031 * accommodate new entries. If the table is emptied below <em>one fourth</em> of
032 * the load factor, it is halved in size. However, halving is not performed when
033 * deleting entries from an iterator, as it would interfere with the iteration
034 * process.
035 * </p>
036 * <p>
037 * Note that {@link #clear()} does not modify the hash table size. Rather, a
038 * family of {@linkplain #trim() trimming methods} lets you control the size of
039 * the table; this is particularly useful if you reuse instances of this class.
040 * </p>
041 * <p>
042 * Iterators generated by this set will enumerate elements in the same order in
043 * which they have been added to the set (addition of elements already present
044 * in the set does not change the iteration order). Note that this order has
045 * nothing in common with the natural order of the keys. The order is kept by
046 * means of an array list, represented <i>via</i> an IntVLA parallel to the
047 * table that can be modified with methods like {@link #shuffle(IRNG)}.
048 * </p>
049 * <p>
050 * This class implements the interface of a sorted set, so to allow easy access
051 * of the iteration order: for instance, you can get the first element in
052 * iteration order with {@code first()} without having to create an iterator;
053 * however, this class partially violates the {@link java.util.SortedSet}
054 * contract because all subset methods throw an exception and
055 * {@link #comparator()} returns always <code>null</code>.
056 * <p>
057 * <p>
058 * Additional methods, such as <code>addAndMoveToFirst()</code>, make it easy to
059 * use instances of this class as a cache (e.g., with LRU policy).
060 * </p>
061 * <p>
062 * This class allows approximately constant-time lookup of keys or values by their index in the ordering, which can
063 * allow some novel usage of the data structure. OrderedSet can be used like a list of unique elements, keeping order
064 * like a list does but also allowing rapid checks for whether an item exists in the OrderedSet, and {@link OrderedMap}
065 * can be used like that but with values associated as well (where OrderedSet uses contains(), OrderedMap uses
066 * containsKey()). You can also set the item at a position with {@link #addAt(Object, int)}, or alter an item while
067 * keeping index the same with {@link #alter(Object, Object)}. Reordering works here too, both with completely random
068 * orders from {@link #shuffle(IRNG)} or with a previously-generated ordering from {@link #reorder(int...)} (you can
069 * produce such an ordering for a given size and reuse it across multiple Ordered data structures with
070 * {@link IRNG#randomOrdering(int)}).
071 * </p>
072 * <p>
073 * You can pass an {@link CrossHash.IHasher} instance such as {@link CrossHash#generalHasher} as an extra parameter to
074 * most of this class' constructors, which allows the OrderedSet to use arrays (usually primitive arrays) as items. If
075 * you expect only one type of array, you can use an instance like {@link CrossHash#intHasher} to hash int arrays, or
076 * the aforementioned generalHasher to hash most kinds of arrays (it can't handle most multi-dimensional arrays well).
077 * If you aren't using array items, you don't need to give an IHasher to the constructor and can ignore this feature.
078 * </p>
079 * <br>
080 * Thank you, Sebastiano Vigna, for making FastUtil available to the public with such high quality.
081 * <br>
082 * See https://github.com/vigna/fastutil for the original library.
083 *
084 * @author Sebastiano Vigna (responsible for all the hard parts)
085 * @author Tommy Ettinger (mostly responsible for squashing several layers of parent classes into one monster class)
086 */

142    /**
143     * Creates a new hash map.
144     * <p>
145     * <p>The actual table size will be the least power of two greater than <code>expected</code>/<code>f</code>.
146     *
147     * @param expected the expected number of elements in the hash set.
148     * @param f        the load factor.
149     */
150
151    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
152    public OrderedSet(final int expected, final float f) {
153        if (f <= 0 || f > 1)
154            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Load factor must be greater than 0 and smaller than or equal to 1");
155        if (expected < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("The expected number of elements must be nonnegative");
156        this.f = f;
157        n = arraySize(expected, f);
158        mask = n - 1;
159        maxFill = maxFill(n, f);
160        key = (K[]) new Object[n + 1];
161        //link = new long[n + 1];
162        order = new IntVLA(expected);
163        hasher = CrossHash.mildHasher;
164    }

408    private int realSize() {
409        return containsNull ? size - 1 : size;
410    }

412    private void ensureCapacity(final int capacity) {
413        final int needed = arraySize(capacity, f);
414        if (needed > n)
415            rehash(needed);
416    }
417
418    private void tryCapacity(final long capacity) {
419        final int needed = (int) Math.min(
420                1 << 30,
421                Math.max(2, HashCommon.nextPowerOfTwo((long) Math.ceil(capacity
422                        / f))));
423        if (needed > n)
424            rehash(needed);
425    }

427    public boolean addAll(Collection<? extends K> c) {
428        int n = c.size();
429        // The resulting collection will be at least c.size() big
430        if (f <= .5)
431            ensureCapacity(n); // The resulting collection will be sized
432            // for c.size() elements
433        else
434            tryCapacity(size() + n); // The resulting collection will be
435        // tentatively sized for size() + c.size() elements
436        boolean retVal = false;
437        final Iterator<? extends K> i = c.iterator();
438        while (n-- != 0)
439            if (add(i.next()))
440                retVal = true;
441        return retVal;
442    }
443
444    public boolean addAll(K[] a) {
445        if(a == null)
446            return false;
447        int n = a.length;
448        // The resulting collection will be at least a.length big
449        if (f <= .5)
450            ensureCapacity(n); // The resulting collection will be sized
451            // for a.length elements
452        else
453            tryCapacity(size() + n); // The resulting collection will be
454        // tentatively sized for size() + a.length elements
455        boolean retVal = false;
456        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
457            if(add(a[i]))
458                retVal = true;
459        }
460        return retVal;
461    }

464    public boolean add(final K k) {
465        int pos;
466        if (k == null) {
467            if (containsNull)
468                return false;
469            pos = n;
470            containsNull = true;
471        } else {
472            K curr;
473            final K[] key = this.key;
474            // The starting point.
475            if (!((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)) {
476                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k))
477                    return false;
478                while (!((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null))
479                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k))
480                        return false;
481            }
482            key[pos] = k;
483        }
484        order.add(pos);
485        if (size++ >= maxFill)
486            rehash(arraySize(size + 1, f));
487        return true;
488    }

490    public boolean addAt(final K k, final int idx) {
491//        if (idx <= 0)
492//            return addAndMoveToFirst(k);
493//        else if (idx >= size)
494//            return addAndMoveToLast(k);
495
496        int pos;
497        if (k == null) {
498            if (containsNull)
499                return false;
500            pos = n;
501            containsNull = true;
502        } else {
503            K curr;
504            final K[] key = this.key;
505            // The starting point.
506            if (!((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)) {
507                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k))
508                    return false;
509                while (!((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null))
510                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k))
511                        return false;
512            }
513            key[pos] = k;
514        }
515        order.insert(idx, pos);
516        if (size++ >= maxFill)
517            rehash(arraySize(size + 1, f));
518        return true;
519    }

521    /**
522     * Add a random element if not present, get the existing value if already
523     * present.
524     * <p>
525     * This is equivalent to (but faster than) doing a:
526     * <p>
527     * <pre>
528     * K exist = set.get(k);
529     * if (exist == null) {
530     *  set.add(k);
531     *  exist = k;
532     * }
533     * </pre>
534     */
535    public K addOrGet(final K k) {
536        int pos;
537        if (k == null) {
538            if (containsNull)
539                return key[n];
540            pos = n;
541            containsNull = true;
542        } else {
543            K curr;
544            final K[] key = this.key;
545            // The starting point.
546            if (!((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)) {
547                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k))
548                    return curr;
549                while (!((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null))
550                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k))
551                        return curr;
552            }
553            key[pos] = k;
554        }
555        order.add(pos);
556        if (size++ >= maxFill)
557            rehash(arraySize(size + 1, f));
558        return k;
559    }

561    /**
562     * Shifts left entries with the specified hash code, starting at the
563     * specified position, and empties the resulting free entry.
564     *
565     * @param pos a starting position.
566     */
567    protected final void shiftKeys(int pos) {
568        // Shift entries with the same hash.
569        int last, slot;
570        K curr;
571        final K[] key = this.key;
572        for (; ; ) {
573            pos = (last = pos) + 1 & mask;
574            for (; ; ) {
575                if ((curr = key[pos]) == null) {
576                    key[last] = null;
577                    return;
578                }
579                slot = (hasher.hash(curr))
580                        & mask;
581                if (last <= pos ? last >= slot || slot > pos : last >= slot
582                        && slot > pos)
583                    break;
584                pos = pos + 1 & mask;
585            }
586            key[last] = curr;
587            fixOrder(pos, last);
588        }
589    }
590
591    private boolean removeEntry(final int pos) {
592        size--;
593        fixOrder(pos);
594        shiftKeys(pos);
595        if (size < maxFill / 4 && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
596            rehash(n / 2);
597        return true;
598    }
599
600    private boolean removeNullEntry() {
601        containsNull = false;
602        key[n] = null;
603        size--;
604        fixOrder(n);
605        if (size < maxFill / 4 && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
606            rehash(n / 2);
607        return true;
608    }
609
610    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
611    protected boolean rem(final Object k) {
612        if (k == null)
613            return containsNull && removeNullEntry();
614        K curr;
615        final K[] key = this.key;
616        int pos;
617        // The starting point.
618        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
619            return false;
620        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
621            return removeEntry(pos);
622        while (true) {
623            if ((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null)
624                return false;
625            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
626                return removeEntry(pos);
627        }
628    }

630    @Override
631    public boolean remove(final Object o) {
632        return rem(o);
633    }

635    /**
636     * Removes the first key in iteration order.
637     *
638     * @return the first key.
639     * @throws NoSuchElementException is this set is empty.
640     */
641    public K removeFirst() {
642        if (size == 0)
643            throw new NoSuchElementException();
644        final int pos = order.removeIndex(0);
645        final K k = key[pos];
646        size--;
647        if (k == null) {
648            containsNull = false;
649            key[n] = null;
650        } else
651            shiftKeys(pos);
652        if (size < maxFill / 4 && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
653            rehash(n / 2);
654        return k;
655    }

657    /**
658     * Removes the the last key in iteration order.
659     *
660     * @return the last key.
661     * @throws NoSuchElementException is this set is empty.
662     */
663    public K removeLast() {
664        if (size == 0)
665            throw new NoSuchElementException();
666        final int pos = order.pop();
667
668        // Abbreviated version of fixOrder(pos)
669        /*
670        last = (int) (link[pos] >>> 32);
671        if (0 <= last) {
672            // Special case of SET_NEXT( link[ last ], -1 )
673            link[last] |= -1 & 0xFFFFFFFFL;
674        }*/
675        final K k = key[pos];
676        size--;
677        if (k == null) {
678            containsNull = false;
679            key[n] = null;
680        } else
681            shiftKeys(pos);
682        if (size < maxFill / 4 && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
683            rehash(n / 2);
684        return k;
685
686    }

688    private void moveIndexToFirst(final int i) {
689        if (size <= 1 || order.items[0] == i)
690            return;
691        order.moveToFirst(i);
692    }

694    private void moveIndexToLast(final int i) {
695        if (size <= 1 || order.items[order.size-1] == i)
696            return;
697        order.moveToLast(i);

700    /**
701     * Adds a key to the set; if the key is already present, it is moved to the
702     * first position of the iteration order.
703     *
704     * @param k the key.
705     * @return true if the key was not present.
706     */
707    public boolean addAndMoveToFirst(final K k) {
708        int pos;
709        if (k == null) {
710            if (containsNull) {
711                moveIndexToFirst(n);
712                return false;
713            }
714            containsNull = true;
715            pos = n;
716        } else {
717            // The starting point.
718            final K[] key = this.key;
719            pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask;
720            while (!(key[pos] == null)) {
721                if (hasher.areEqual(k, key[pos])) {
722                    moveIndexToFirst(pos);
723                    return false;
724                }
725                pos = pos + 1 & mask;
726            }
727        }
728        key[pos] = k;
729        order.insert(0, pos);
730        if (size++ >= maxFill)
731            rehash(arraySize(size, f));
732        return true;
733    }

736     * Adds a key to the set; if the key is already present, it is moved to the
737     * last position of the iteration order.
738     *
739     * @param k the key.
740     * @return true if the key was not present.
741     */
742    public boolean addAndMoveToLast(final K k) {
743        int pos;
744        if (k == null) {
745            if (containsNull) {
746                moveIndexToLast(n);
747                return false;
748            }
749            containsNull = true;
750            pos = n;
751        } else {
752            // The starting point.
753            final K[] key = this.key;
754            pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask;
755            // There's always an unused entry.
756            while (!(key[pos] == null)) {
757                if (hasher.areEqual(k, key[pos])) {
758                    moveIndexToLast(pos);
759                    return false;
760                }
761                pos = pos + 1 & mask;
762            }
763        }
764        key[pos] = k;
765        order.add(pos);
766        if (size++ >= maxFill)
767            rehash(arraySize(size, f));
768        return true;

771    /**
772     * Returns the element of this set that is equal to the given key, or
773     * <code>null</code>.
774     *
775     * @return the element of this set that is equal to the given key, or
776     * <code>null</code>.
777     */
778    public K get(final Object k) {
779        if (k == null)
780            return key[n]; // This is correct independently of the value of
781        // containsNull and of the map being custom
782        K curr;
783        final K[] key = this.key;
784        int pos;
785        // The starting point.
786        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
787            return null;
788        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
789            return curr;
790        // There's always an unused entry.
791        while (true) {
792            if ((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null)
793                return null;
794            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
795                return curr;
796        }
797    }

799    public boolean contains(final Object k) {
800        if (k == null)
801            return containsNull;
802        K curr;
803        final K[] key = this.key;
804        int pos;
805        // The starting point.
806        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
807            return false;
808        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
809            return true;
810        // There's always an unused entry.
811        while (true) {
812            if ((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null)
813                return false;
814            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
815                return true;
816        }

820        if (k == null)
821        {
822            if(containsNull)
823                return n;
824            else
825                return -1;
826        }
827        K curr;
828        final K[] key = this.key;
829        int pos;
830        // The starting point.
831        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
832            return -1;
833        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
834            return pos;
835        // There's always an unused entry.
836        while (true) {
837            if ((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null)
838                return -1;
839            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
840                return pos;
841        }

857     * Swaps the positions in the ordering for the given items, if they are both present. Returns true if the ordering
858     * changed as a result of this call, or false if it stayed the same (which can be because left or right was not
859     * present, or because left and right are the same reference (so swapping would do nothing)).
860     * @param left an item that should be present in this OrderedSet
861     * @param right an item that should be present in this OrderedSet
862     * @return true if this OrderedSet changed in ordering as a result of this call, or false otherwise
863     */
864    public boolean swap(final K left, final K right)
865    {
866        if(left == right) return false;
867        int l = indexOf(left);
868        if(l < 0) return false;
869        int r = indexOf(right);
870        if(r < 0) return false;
871        order.swap(l, r);
872        return true;

882    public boolean swapIndices(final int left, final int right)

884        if(left < 0 || right < 0 || left >= order.size || right >= order.size || left == right) return false;

1040    /**
1041     * A list iterator over a linked set.
1042     * <p>
1043     * <p>
1044     * This class provides a list iterator over a linked hash set. The
1045     * constructor runs in constant time.
1046     */
1047    private class SetIterator implements ListIterator<K> {
1048        /**
1049         * The entry that will be returned by the next call to
1050         * {@link java.util.ListIterator#previous()} (or <code>null</code> if no
1051         * previous entry exists).
1052         */
1053        int prev = -1;
1054        /**
1055         * The entry that will be returned by the next call to
1056         * {@link java.util.ListIterator#next()} (or <code>null</code> if no
1057         * next entry exists).
1058         */
1059        int next = -1;
1060        /**
1061         * The last entry that was returned (or -1 if we did not iterate or used
1062         * {@link #remove()}).
1063         */
1064        int curr = -1;
1065        /**
1066         * The current index (in the sense of a {@link java.util.ListIterator}).
1067         * When -1, we do not know the current index.
1068         */
1069        int index = -1;
1070
1071        SetIterator() {
1072            next = size == 0 ? -1 : order.items[0];
1073            index = 0;
1074        }
1075
1076        public boolean hasNext() {
1077            return next != -1;
1078        }
1079
1080        public boolean hasPrevious() {
1081            return prev != -1;
1082        }
1083
1084        public K next() {
1085            if (!hasNext())
1086                throw new NoSuchElementException();
1087            curr = next;
1088            if (++index >= order.size)
1089                next = -1;
1090            else
1091                next = order.get(index);//(int) link[curr];
1092            prev = curr;
1093            return key[curr];
1094        }
1095
1096        public K previous() {
1097            if (!hasPrevious())
1098                throw new NoSuchElementException();
1099            curr = prev;
1100            if (--index < 1)
1101                prev = -1;
1102            else
1103                prev = order.get(index - 1);
1104            next = curr;
1105            return key[curr];
1106        }
1107
1108        private void ensureIndexKnown() {
1109            if (index >= 0)
1110                return;
1111            if (prev == -1) {
1112                index = 0;
1113                return;
1114            }
1115            if (next == -1) {
1116                index = size;
1117                return;
1118            }
1119            index = 0;
1120        }
1121
1122        public int nextIndex() {
1123            ensureIndexKnown();
1124            return index + 1;
1125        }
1126
1127        public int previousIndex() {
1128            ensureIndexKnown();
1129            return index - 1;
1130        }
1131
1132        public void remove() {
1133            ensureIndexKnown();
1134            if (curr == -1)
1135                throw new IllegalStateException();
1136            if (curr == prev) {
1137                /*
1138                 * If the last operation was a next(), we are removing an entry
1139                                 * that precedes the current index, and thus we must decrement
1140                                 * it.
1141                                 */
1142                if (--index >= 1)
1143                    prev = order.get(index - 1); //(int) (link[curr] >>> 32);
1144                else
1145                    prev = -1;
1146            } else {
1147                if (index < order.size - 1)
1148                    next = order.get(index + 1);
1149                else
1150                    next = -1;
1151            }
1152            order.removeIndex(index);
1153            size--;
1154            int last, slot, pos = curr;
1155            curr = -1;
1156            if (pos == n) {
1157                containsNull = false;
1158                key[n] = null;
1159                //order.removeValue(pos);
1160            } else {
1161                K curr;
1162                final K[] key = OrderedSet.this.key;
1163                // We have to horribly duplicate the shiftKeys() code because we
1164                // need to update next/prev.
1165                for (; ; ) {
1166                    pos = (last = pos) + 1 & mask;
1167                    for (; ; ) {
1168                        if ((curr = key[pos]) == null) {
1169                            key[last] = null;
1170                            return;
1171                        }
1172                        slot = (hasher.hash(curr)) & mask;
1173                        if (last <= pos
1174                                ? last >= slot || slot > pos
1175                                : last >= slot && slot > pos)
1176                            break;
1177                        pos = pos + 1 & mask;
1178                    }
1179                    key[last] = curr;
1180                    if (next == pos)
1181                        next = last;
1182                    if (prev == pos)
1183                        prev = last;
1184                    fixOrder(pos, last);
1185                }
1186            }
1187
1188        }

1403    /**
1404     * Returns a hash code for this set.
1405     * <p>
1406     * This method overrides the generic method provided by the superclass.
1407     * Since <code>equals()</code> is not overriden, it is important that the
1408     * value returned by this method is the same value as the one returned by
1409     * the overriden method.
1410     *
1411     * @return a hash code for this set.
1412     */
1413    public int hashCode() {
1414        int h = 0;
1415        for (int j = realSize(), i = 0; j-- != 0; ) {
1416            while (key[i] == null)
1417                i++;
1418            if (this != key[i])
1419                h += hasher.hash(key[i]);
1420            i++;
1421        }
1422        // Zero / null have hash zero.
1423        return h;
1424    }

1426    public long hash64()
1427    {
1428        long seed = 9069147967908697017L;
1429        final int len = order.size;
1430        final int[] data = order.items;
1431        for (int i = 3; i < len; i+=4) {
1432            seed = mum(
1433                    mum(Objects.hashCode(key[data[i-3]]) ^ b1, Objects.hashCode(key[data[i-2]]) ^ b2) + seed,
1434                    mum(Objects.hashCode(key[data[i-1]]) ^ b3, Objects.hashCode(key[data[i]]) ^ b4));
1435        }
1436        switch (len & 3) {
1437            case 0: seed = mum(b1 ^ seed, b4 + seed); break;
1438            case 1: seed = mum(seed ^ Objects.hashCode(key[data[len-1]]) >>> 16, b3 ^ (Objects.hashCode(key[data[len-1]]) & 0xFFFFL)); break;
1439            case 2: seed = mum(seed ^ Objects.hashCode(key[data[len-2]]), b0 ^ Objects.hashCode(key[data[len-1]])); break;
1440            case 3: seed = mum(seed ^ Objects.hashCode(key[data[len-3]]), b2 ^ Objects.hashCode(key[data[len-2]])) ^ mum(seed ^ Objects.hashCode(key[data[len-1]]), b4); break;
1441        }
1442        seed = (seed ^ seed << 16) * (len ^ b0);
1443        return seed - (seed >>> 31) + (seed << 33);
1444    }

1453    public static int maxFill(final int n, final float f) {
1454        /* We must guarantee that there is always at least

1473     * Returns the least power of two smaller than or equal to 2<sup>30</sup> and larger than or equal to <code>Math.ceil( expected / f )</code>.
1474     *
1475     * @param expected the expected number of elements in a hash table.
1476     * @param f        the load factor.
1477     * @return the minimum possible size for a backing array.
1478     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the necessary size is larger than 2<sup>30</sup>.
1479     */
1480    public static int arraySize(final int expected, final float f) {
1481        final long s = Math.max(2, HashCommon.nextPowerOfTwo((long) Math.ceil(expected / f)));
1482        if (s > 1 << 30)
1483            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Too large (" + expected + " expected elements with load factor " + f + ")");
1484        return (int) s;

1505    /**
1506     * Unwraps an iterator into an array starting at a given offset for a given number of elements.
1507     * <p>
1508     * <P>This method iterates over the given type-specific iterator and stores the elements returned, up to a maximum of <code>length</code>, in the given array starting at <code>offset</code>. The
1509     * number of actually unwrapped elements is returned (it may be less than <code>max</code> if the iterator emits less than <code>max</code> elements).
1510     *
1511     * @param i      a type-specific iterator.
1512     * @param array  an array to contain the output of the iterator.
1513     * @param offset the first element of the array to be returned.
1514     * @param max    the maximum number of elements to unwrap.
1515     * @return the number of elements unwrapped.
1516     */
1517    private static <K> int objectUnwrap(final Iterator<? extends K> i, final K[] array, int offset, final int max) {
1518        if (max < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("The maximum number of elements (" + max + ") is negative");
1519        if (offset < 0 || offset + max > array.length) throw new IllegalArgumentException();
1520        int j = max;
1521        while (j-- != 0 && i.hasNext())
1522            array[offset++] = i.next();
1523        return max - j - 1;
1524    }

1577    @GwtIncompatible
1578    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
1579    private void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream s)
1580            throws java.io.IOException, ClassNotFoundException {
1581        s.defaultReadObject();
1582        n = arraySize(size, f);
1583        maxFill = maxFill(n, f);
1584        mask = n - 1;
1585        final K[] key = this.key = (K[]) new Object[n + 1];
1586        final IntVLA order = this.order = new IntVLA(n + 1);
1587        K k;
1588        for (int i = size, pos; i-- != 0; ) {
1589            k = (K) s.readObject();
1590            if (k == null) {
1591                pos = n;
1592                containsNull = true;
1593            } else {
1594                if (!(key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask] == null))
1595                    while (!(key[pos = pos + 1 & mask] == null)) ;
1596            }
1597            key[pos] = k;
1598            order.add(pos);
1599        }
1600    }

1680    private boolean alterEntry(final int pos, final K replacement) {
1681        int rep;
1682        if (replacement == null) {
1683            if (containsNull)
1684                return false;
1685            rep = n;
1686            containsNull = true;
1687        } else {
1688            K curr;
1689            final K[] key = this.key;
1690            shiftKeys(pos);
1691            // The starting point.
1692            if (!((curr = key[rep = (hasher.hash(replacement)) & mask]) == null)) {
1693                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
1694                    return false;
1695                while (!((curr = key[rep = rep + 1 & mask]) == null))
1696                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
1697                        return false;
1698            }
1699            key[rep] = replacement;
1700        }
1701        fixOrder(pos, rep);
1702        return true;
1703    }

1774    /**
1775     * Changes a K, original, to another, replacement, while keeping replacement at the same point in the ordering.
1776     *
1777     * @param original    a K value that will be removed from this Set if present, and its iteration index remembered
1778     * @param replacement another K value that will replace original at the remembered index
1779     * @return true if the Set changed, or false if it didn't (such as if the two arguments are equal, or replacement was already in the Set but original was not)
1780     */
1781    public boolean alter(K original, K replacement) {
1782        int idx;
1783        if (original == null) {
1784            if (containsNull) {
1785                if (replacement != null) {
1786                    idx = alterNullEntry();
1787                    addAt(replacement, idx);
1788                    return true;
1789                } else
1790                    return false;
1791            }
1792            ;
1793            return false;
1794        }
1795        if (hasher.areEqual(original, replacement))
1796            return false;

1798        final K[] key = this.key;
1799        int pos;
